How to Treat Incontinence Without Hormone Therapy or Kegel Exercises in Just 3 Days

Plus: How you can easily do this from the comfort of your own home, restoring control over your bladder and ensuring no more embarrassing leaks...

﻿

WITHOUT expensive injections, surgery, or chemical medications that could harm your body or cause irritation.

By Dr. Anna Pearson | 26 May 2025 | 11:18


One of the most embarrassing moments you can experience...


You feel tired, so you lie down for a moment...


And before you know it, you drift off to sleep.


But as soon as you wake up, you feel that awful sensation...


The feeling of a cold, wet patch around you.


Because incontinence isn't something we can always control.


And it doesn’t just make you feel ashamed...


It’s also one of the most exhausting conditions to live with.


Especially if you're constantly trying to avoid embarrassing situations...


Or always looking for the nearest toilet...


But what if you could treat this permanently from the comfort of your own home?


Thanks to a recent study from the South Africa medical research centre...


Researchers have uncovered an unexpected cause of incontinence.


The real reason behind bladder control loss...


And based on this discovery, dermatologist Dr. Pearson has developed a product that doesn’t just restore control...


But also does this...

Eliminates the burning sensation

Makes your bladder feel completely empty

Reduces the 'pressure' feeling on your bladder

Eases the stress of potential accidents

Eliminates uncomfortable odours

And that’s what makes it so special...

You can regain control of your bladder in just a few minutes and avoid embarrassing leaks from the comfort of your own home—without using pads, chemical medications, or surgery.


It’s fast, easy, affordable, and best of all—you can do it from home.

Dr. Catherine Lewis


I am a certified gynaecologist with 23 years of experience.


My specialisation is in incontinence.


My patients range from older individuals to women who have experienced vaginal health issues and reach out to me for advice regarding incontinence—or even considering surgery.

In this article, I will share my latest discovery about incontinence and bladder control.

Why most solutions don’t work

Before we talk about how to treat incontinence, there’s something important you need to understand…


Most incontinence treatments can actually be harmful to the skin.


Take incontinence pads, for example—they constantly expose your body to moisture, which can lead to irritation and infections.


You’ve probably heard before that you should do bladder exercises or lose weight.


Or that Botox injections or hormone therapies are the ultimate solution for treating incontinence.


But there’s just one problem—these only address the symptoms, not the root cause…

What is the real cause of incontinence?

Incontinence occurs when the nerves in the bladder wall lose their ability to activate properly.


Now, you might be wondering, “Why do these nerves lose function?”


Let me explain…


As we age, oestrogen levels in the body naturally decline.


This means the bladder wall receives fewer nutrients and becomes thinner.


As a result, the underlying nerves become more vulnerable to damage.


When these nerves weaken, they lose strength and function.


This also means the pelvic floor muscles become less active, making it harder to prevent leakage…

And there’s more…

As we get older, it becomes harder for our body to reactivate these underlying nerves...


Especially as oestrogen levels continue to decline with age.


This is why incontinence tends to get worse year after year.


As a result, you may feel like you can’t leave the house without wearing a pad or incontinence protection.


And the worst part? Without it, you live in constant stress, worrying about unwanted leaks...


That’s why we need to strengthen the nerves in the bladder wall to restore control over the pelvic floor muscles.


Otherwise, you’ll never be able to fully treat incontinence.

Here’s the good news…

Remember when I told you about the recent discovery from a leading South Africa medical research centre?


Well, this South Africa-based institute has identified an ingredient that strengthens the underlying nerves in the bladder wall.


Helping you regain control over your pelvic floor muscles.

As seen in...

This ingredient is L-Carnitine, known for its restorative and regenerative properties.


This ingredient has been used for years in the South Africa health industry.


During a South Africa-based medical study, researchers discovered that L-Carnitine enhances energy supply to nerve cells, speeding up their recovery.


Additionally, it helps rebuild the protective layer around the nerves, reducing the risk of damage.


Once the nerve cells have fully recovered, you regain control over your pelvic floor muscles—and ultimately, over your bladder.


So, if you want to treat incontinence, increasing your intake of L-Carnitine is the key solution.


Unfortunately, the market is flooded with similar products, so how do you know which one will deliver real results?

How to choose the right product

The best way is to choose a product that contains clinically proven natural ingredients.


There are two key factors to consider when selecting an L-Carnitine supplement.


Here’s what you need to look for...

Is the manufacturer of your product cGMP certified?

This is the gold standard for quality.


cGMP stands for ‘Current Good Manufacturing Practice’, ensuring that the product is manufactured under strict safety regulations—preventing contamination and bacterial growth. This is especially crucial for products used near intimate areas.


You might be surprised to learn that the South Africa’s Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) has received multiple complaints about major health brands causing severe vaginal infections.


That’s why it’s essential to choose a product that is cGMP certified. Not all companies invest in this certification, but for me, it’s a non-negotiable priority.

Does the product offer a complete treatment?

It’s not just about repairing the nerves in the bladder wall.


The area around your vagina is highly sensitive, delicate, and fragile.


You don’t just want to regain control over your bladder—you want the effects to be permanent, so you never have to worry about unexpected leaks again.


While L-Carnitine is excellent for restoring nerves in the bladder wall, it alone is not enough.


The product must also contain a healthy combination of bladder-strengthening ingredients and energy-boosting compounds that ensure:

Restores pelvic floor strength

Eliminates skin irritation

Relieves constant bladder pressure

Thickens the bladder wall

Reduces bladder inflammation

Prevents unwanted leaks

That may sound like a lot for one product…


But it is possible when the ingredients are carefully selected and measured in perfect amounts.


These are the two most important criteria for an effective incontinence cream.


The problem: Even with access to the best healthcare products, I struggled to find a cream that met all these requirements.


That’s why I decided to contact one of my most trusted suppliers in the health industry to create a solution that met every standard. It wasn’t easy.


And what I can tell you is…

This process took over two years.

I wanted to personally test each ingredient with my patients.


This way, I could ensure that the product contained the right amount of each ingredient.


For me, it was essential that this formula remained as pure as possible, and that I could guarantee it actually worked.


Secondly, I needed to find a manufacturer I could trust.


Someone who is cGMP-certified and willing to produce this cream with the same level of care that I would.


It took time, but the final result was more than worth it.

And after 32 prototypes, we developed BioEdge™

By applying just a small amount of this L-Carnitine cream to the lower abdomen, just above the pubic area, you’ll feel the constant pressure and minor leaks disappear within 11 minutes.


The small leaks that occur when coughing, sneezing, or laughing stop immediately, and the nerves in the bladder wall begin to repair themselves.

See the difference in just 11 minutes

Curious about how this works so quickly? It’s all thanks to these powerful ingredients.


L-Carnitine


The L-Carnitine in BioEdge™ nourishes the nerves in the bladder wall by increasing energy supply and repairing damaged nerve cells—crucial for maintaining healthy bladder function.


Vitamin B6 & B12


The Vitamin B6 & B12 in BioEdge™ improves oxygen delivery to vaginal tissues, which is essential for bladder wall repair and strengthening.


It also supports the regeneration of myelin, the protective layer around nerves, improving nerve function.


Magnesium


The Magnesium in BioEdge™ promotes relaxation and restores blood flow to bladder tissue, speeding up recovery.


It also relaxes tense muscles and improves pelvic floor contractions.


Omega-3 fatty acids


Omega-3 helps restore nerves in the bladder wall by reducing inflammation and improving blood circulation.


This strengthens the bladder wall by promoting the growth of healthy cells and reinforces the pelvic floor muscles by reducing inflammation in surrounding tissues.

As you can see, we have carefully formulated every ingredient in BioEdge™ to help bring incontinence under control.


Even just one of these powerful ingredients can significantly reduce incontinence and restore bladder control.


But with BioEdge™, you get everything in one convenient cream.


In short, BioEdge™ restores bladder control, reduces unwanted leaks, and strengthens the pelvic floor muscles in just a few days.
